description: French watch brand Bell & Ross is all about watches that put functionality first. Inspired by aviation, these timepieces look sporty and chic, channeling the Mod style of the ‘60s.

Those who love Swiss heritage watches at an affordable price point will fall for Baume & Mercier instantly. The company dates back to 1830; however, its timepieces have a modern feel as well as a sense of tradition.

It’s easy to see why IWC Schaffhausen is one of the most famous watch brands in the world. This prestigious manufacturer is all about attention to detail and has been making timepieces for women since the 1870s.
